9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1220, L.D. 1822, “An Act to Enact the
10 Maine Online Data Privacy Act”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Enact the Maine Consumer Data Privacy Act'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 10 MRSA c. 1057 is enacted to read:
16 CHAPTER 1057
17 MAINE CONSUMER DATA PRIVACY ACT
18 §9601. Short title
19 This chapter may be known and cited as "the Maine Consumer Data Privacy Act."
20 §9602. Definitions
21 As used in this chapter, unless the context otherwise indicates, the following terms
22 have the following meanings.
23 1. Affiliate. "Affiliate" means a business or nonprofit organization that shares
24 common branding with another business or nonprofit organization or controls, is controlled
25 by or is under common control with another business or nonprofit organization.
26 2. Biometric data. "Biometric data" means data generated by automatic
27 measurements of an individual's biological characteristics, such as a fingerprint, voiceprint,
28 retina, iris or other unique biological pattern or characteristic that is used to identify a
29 specific individual. "Biometric data" does not include:
30 A. A digital or physical photograph;
Page 1 - 132LR0014(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1220, L.D. 1822
1 B. An audio or video recording;
2 C. Any data generated from a digital or physical photograph or an audio or video
3 recording, unless the data is generated to identify a specific individual; or
4 D. Data collected, used or stored for health care treatment, payment or operations under
5 the federal Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996, 42 United
6 States Code, Chapter 7, Subchapter XI, Part C, and the regulations, rules, guidance and
7 exemptions adopted pursuant to that Act.
8 3. Business associate. "Business associate" has the same meaning as in 45 Code of
9 Federal Regulations, Section 160.103.
10 4. Child. "Child" means an individual who has not attained 13 years of age.
11 5. Consent. "Consent" means a clear affirmative act signifying a consumer's freely
12 given, specific, informed and unambiguous agreement to allow the processing of personal
13 data relating to the consumer. "Consent" may include a written statement, including by
14 electronic means, that is made in the language the consumer uses to obtain a product or
15 service from the controller and in a format that is reasonably accessible to and usable by
16 consumers with disabilities. "Consent" does not include:
17 A. Acceptance of a terms of use document or similar document that contains
18 descriptions of personal data processing along with other unrelated information;
19 B. Hovering over, muting, pausing or closing a given piece of content; or
20 C. Agreement obtained through the use of a dark pattern.
21 6. Consumer. "Consumer" means an individual who is a resident of this State.
22 "Consumer" does not include an individual acting in a commercial or employment context
23 or as an employee, owner, director, officer or contractor of a company, partnership, sole
24 proprietorship, nonprofit organization or government agency whose communications or
25 transactions with the controller occur solely within the context of that individual's role with
26 the company, partnership, sole proprietorship, nonprofit organization or government
27 agency.
28 7. Control. "Control" means:
29 A. Ownership of, or the power to vote, more than 50% of the outstanding shares of
30 any class of voting security of a company;
31 B. Control in any manner over the election of a majority of the directors of a company
32 or of individuals exercising similar functions in a company; or
33 C. Power to exercise controlling influence over the management of a company.
34 8. Controller. "Controller" means a person that, alone or jointly with other persons,
35 determines the purpose and means of processing personal data.
36 9. COPPA. "COPPA" means the federal Children's Online Privacy Protection Act of
37 1998, 15 United States Code, Section 6501 et seq. and the regulations, rules, guidance and
38 exemptions adopted pursuant to that Act, as that Act and such regulations, rules, guidance
39 and exemptions may be amended from time to time.
40 10. Covered entity. "Covered entity" has the same meaning as in 45 Code of Federal
41 Regulations, Section 160.103.
Page 2 - 132LR0014(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1220, L.D. 1822
1 11. Dark pattern. "Dark pattern" means a user interface designed or manipulated
2 with the substantial effect of subverting or impairing user autonomy, decision-making or
3 choice and includes, but is not limited to, any practice the Federal Trade Commission refers
4 to as a dark pattern.
5 12. Decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects concerning the
6 consumer. "Decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects concerning the
7 consumer" means decisions that result in the provision or denial to the consumer of
8 financial or lending services, housing, insurance, education enrollment or opportunity,
9 criminal justice, employment opportunities, health care services or access to essential
10 goods or services.
11 13. De-identified data. "De-identified data" means data that cannot reasonably be
12 used to infer information about or otherwise be linked to an identified or identifiable
13 individual, or a device linked to an individual, if the controller that possesses the data:
14 A. Takes reasonable measures to ensure that the de-identified data cannot be associated
15 with an individual;
16 B. Publicly commits to process the de-identified data only in a de-identified fashion
17 and not attempt to re-identify the data; and
18 C. Contractually obligates recipients of the de-identified data to satisfy the criteria set
19 forth in paragraphs A and B.
20 14. Federally recognized Indian tribe in this State. "Federally recognized Indian
21 tribe in this State" means the Houlton Band of Maliseet Indians, the Mi'kmaq Nation, the
22 Passamaquoddy Tribe or the Penobscot Nation when the band, nation or tribe is acting in
23 a governmental capacity and not in a business capacity. "Federal recognized Indian tribe
24 in this State" does not include a business entity, including any federally chartered tribal
25 corporation or other business entity owned or partly owned by the Houlton Band of
26 Maliseet Indians, the Mi'kmaq Nation, the Passamaquoddy Tribe or the Penobscot Nation.
27 15. Nonprofit organization. "Nonprofit organization" means an organization that is
28 exempt from taxation under Section 501(c)(3), Section 501(c)(4), Section 501(c)(6) or
29 Section 501(c)(12) of the United States Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended.
30 16. Personal data. "Personal data" means information that is linked or reasonably
31 linkable to an identified or identifiable consumer or that is linked or reasonably linkable to
32 a device that is linked or reasonably linkable to an identified or identifiable consumer.
33 "Personal data" does not include de-identified data or publicly available information.
34 17. Precise geolocation data. "Precise geolocation data" means information derived
35 from technology, including, but not limited to, global positioning system level latitude and
36 longitude coordinates, that directly identifies the specific location of an individual with
37 precision and accuracy within a radius of 1,750 feet. "Precise geolocation data" does not
38 include:
39 A. The content of communications; or
40 B. Data generated by or connected to advanced utility metering infrastructure systems
41 or equipment for use by a utility.
Page 3 - 132LR0014(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1220, L.D. 1822
1 18. Process. "Process" means an operation or set of operations performed on personal
2 data, including the collection, use, storage, disclosure, analysis, deletion or modification of
3 personal data.
4 19. Processor. "Processor" means a person that processes personal data on behalf of
5 a controller.
6 20. Profiling. "Profiling" means any form of solely automated process performed on
7 personal data to evaluate, analyze or predict personal aspects related to an identified or
8 identifiable individual's economic situation, health, personal preferences, interests,
9 reliability, behavior, location or movements.
10 21. Protected health information. "Protected health information" has the same
11 meaning as in the regulations, rules, guidance and exemptions adopted pursuant to the
12 federal Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996, 42 United States
13 Code, Chapter 7, Subchapter XI, Part C.
14 22. Pseudonymous data. "Pseudonymous data" means personal data that cannot be
15 attributed to a specific individual without the use of additional information, as long as the
16 additional information is kept separately from the personal data and is subject to
17 appropriate technical and organizational measures to ensure that the personal data is not
18 attributed to an identified or identifiable individual.
19 23. Publicly available information. "Publicly available information" means
20 information that:
21 A. Is lawfully made available to the general public through federal, state or local
22 government records; or
23 B. Is lawfully made available to the general public through widely distributed media.
24 24. Sale of personal data. "Sale of personal data" means the exchange of personal
25 data for monetary or other valuable consideration by the controller to a 3rd party. "Sale of
26 personal data" does not include:
27 A. The disclosure of personal data to a processor that processes the personal data on
28 behalf of the controller;
29 B. The disclosure of personal data to a 3rd party for purposes of providing a product
30 or service requested by the consumer;
31 C. The disclosure or transfer of personal data to an affiliate of the controller;
32 D. The disclosure of personal data when the consumer directs the controller to disclose
33 the personal data or intentionally uses the controller to interact with a 3rd party;
34 E. The disclosure of personal data that the consumer:
35 (1) Intentionally made available to the general public via a channel of mass media;
36 and
37 (2) Did not restrict to a specific audience; or
38 F. The disclosure or transfer of personal data to a 3rd party as an asset that is part of a
39 merger, acquisition, bankruptcy or other transaction, or a proposed merger, acquisition,
40 bankruptcy or other transaction, in which the 3rd party assumes control of all or part
41 of the controller's assets.
Page 4 - 132LR0014(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1220, L.D. 1822
1 25. Sensitive data. "Sensitive data" means personal data that includes:
2 A. Data revealing racial or ethnic origins, religious beliefs, medical history, mental or
3 physical health conditions, diagnoses made by a medical professional, sexual
4 orientation or citizenship or immigration status;
5 B. Genetic or biometric data;
6 C. Personal data collected from a consumer known to be a child;
7 D. Precise geolocation data;
8 E. A social security number, driver's license number or nondriver identification card
9 number, except that "sensitive data" does not include the last 4 digits of a social security
10 number, driver's license number or nondriver identification card number;
11 F. A consumer's account number, log-in information, financial account number or
12 credit or debit card number that, in combination with any required security code, access
13 code or password, permits access to a consumer's financial account; or
14 G. Data concerning an individual's status as a victim of a crime. For the purposes of
15 this paragraph, "victim" has the same meaning as in Title 17-A, section 2101,
16 subsection 2.
17 26. Targeted advertising. "Targeted advertising" means displaying an advertisement
18 to a consumer when the advertisement is selected based on personal data obtained or
19 inferred from that consumer's activities over time and across nonaffiliated publicly
20 accessible websites or online applications to predict that consumer's preferences or
21 interests. "Targeted advertising" does not include:
22 A. Advertisements based on activities within a controller's own publicly accessible
23 websites or online applications;
24 B. Advertisements based on the context of a consumer's current search query, visit to
25 a publicly accessible website or online application;
26 C. Advertisements directed to a consumer in response to the consumer's request for
27 information or feedback; or
28 D. Processing personal data solely to measure or report advertising frequency,
29 performance or reach.
30 27. Trade secret. "Trade secret" has the same meaning as in section 1542, subsection
31 4.
32 §9603. Scope
33 1. Applicability; July 1, 2026 to December 31, 2027. From July 1, 2026 to December
34 31, 2027, the provisions of this chapter apply to persons that conduct business in this State
35 or persons that produce products or services that are targeted to residents of this State and
36 that during the preceding calendar year:
37 A. Controlled or processed the personal data of not less than 100,000 consumers,
38 excluding personal data controlled or processed solely for the purpose of completing a
39 payment transaction; or
40 B. Controlled or processed the personal data of not less than 25,000 consumers and
41 derived more than 25% of gross revenue from the sale of personal data.
Page 5 - 132LR0014(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1220, L.D. 1822
1 2. Applicability; beginning January 1, 2028. Beginning January 1, 2028, the
2 provisions of this chapter apply to persons that conduct business in this State or persons
3 that produce products or services that are targeted to residents of this State and that during
4 the preceding calendar year:
5 A. Controlled or processed the personal data of not less than 50,000 consumers,
6 excluding personal data controlled or processed solely for the purpose of completing a
7 payment transaction; or
8 B. Controlled or processed the personal data of not less than 25,000 consumers and
9 derived more than 25% of gross revenue from the sale of personal data.
10 3. Exempt entities. The provisions of this chapter do not apply to:
11 A. A body, authority, board, bureau, commission, district or agency of this State, a
12 political subdivision of this State or a federally recognized Indian tribe in this State;
13 B. A national securities association that is registered under the federal Securities
14 Exchange Act of 1934, 15 United States Code, Section 78a et seq.;
15 C. A financial institution or affiliate of a financial institution, including a service
16 corporation, that is subject to Title V of the federal Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act, 15
17 United States Code, Section 6801 et seq. (1999), as amended;
18 D. A person or entity that qualifies as a licensee under Title 24-A, section 2263,
19 subsection 8;
20 E. A covered entity or business associate;
21 F. A nonprofit organization that:
22 (1) Does not receive any revenue from the sale of personal data; or
23 (2) That is established to detect and prevent fraudulent acts in connection with
24 insurance; or
25 G. A person or entity that is a motor vehicle dealer franchisee as described in section
26 1171, subsection 7.
27 4. Exempt data. The provisions of this chapter do not apply to:
28 A. Nonpublic personal information regulated under and collected, processed, sold or
29 disclosed in accordance with the requirements of the federal Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act,
30 15 United States Code, Section 6801 et seq. (1999), as amended;
31 B. Health care information as defined in Title 22, section 1711-C, subsection 1,
32 paragraph E;
33 C. Protected health information under the federal Health Insurance Portability and
34 Accountability Act of 1996, 42 United States Code, Chapter 7, Subchapter XI, Part C,
35 and the regulations, rules, guidance and exemptions adopted pursuant to that Act;
36 D. Patient-identifying information as described in 42 United States Code, Section
37 290dd-2;
38 E. Identifiable private information for the protection of human subjects in research
39 under 45 Code of Federal Regulations, Part 46;
